<subSubSection pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1436,1510,2008]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1510,1535]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species differs from the other species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[906,1057,1510,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Leucophenga" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[906,1057,1510,1534]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Leucophenga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the epandrium dorsally strongly expanded (
<figureCitation box="[372,477,1546,1571]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="55.[151,250,1939,1961]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,451,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-149@55.[151,1437,447,1917]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURE 34. Leucophenga platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia in lateral view. A. Epandrium, surstylus, and cercus; B. Hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus, and aedeagal apodeme; C. Paramere; D. Aedeagus. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297956/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 34A</figureCitation>
); aedeagus thick, wrinkled, and distally broadened (
<figureCitation box="[1059,1164,1546,1571]" captionStart="FIGURE 34" captionStartId="55.[151,250,1939,1961]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,451,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-149@55.[151,1437,447,1917]" captionTargetPageId="55" captionText="FIGURE 34. Leucophenga platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov., male terminalia in lateral view. A. Epandrium, surstylus, and cercus; B. Hypandrium, paramere, gonopods, aedeagus, and aedeagal apodeme; C. Paramere; D. Aedeagus. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297956" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297956/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 34D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="55" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="54.[151,1436,1510,2008]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1582,1607]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Description.</emphasis>
Ocellar triangle brownish, with ca. 5 setae above ocellar setae. Frons brownish. Pedicel brownish yellow (
<figureCitation box="[247,341,1618,1643]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[287,1308,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-106@21.[284,1309,193,1927]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga hyaloptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; D, E, F. L. oxyptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. serrateiceps Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. valvata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov; P, Q, R. L. zebrina Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297910/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 8G</figureCitation>
); first flagellomere yellow (
<figureCitation box="[672,767,1618,1643]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[287,1308,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-106@21.[284,1309,193,1927]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga hyaloptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; D, E, F. L. oxyptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. serrateiceps Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. valvata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov; P, Q, R. L. zebrina Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297910/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 8G</figureCitation>
). Clypeus entirely dark yellow. Palpus yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1328,1423,1618,1643]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[287,1308,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-106@21.[284,1309,193,1927]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga hyaloptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; D, E, F. L. oxyptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. serrateiceps Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. valvata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov; P, Q, R. L. zebrina Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297910/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 8G</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum mostly brownish yellow (
<figureCitation box="[582,673,1654,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[287,1308,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-106@21.[284,1309,193,1927]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga hyaloptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; D, E, F. L. oxyptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. serrateiceps Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. valvata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov; P, Q, R. L. zebrina Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297910/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 8H</figureCitation>
). Postpronotal lobe dark yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1050,1129,1654,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[287,1308,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-106@21.[284,1309,193,1927]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga hyaloptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; D, E, F. L. oxyptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. serrateiceps Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. valvata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov; P, Q, R. L. zebrina Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297910/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 8I</figureCitation>
). Acrostichal setulae in ca. 8–10 irregular rows (
<figureCitation box="[416,515,1690,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[287,1308,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-106@21.[284,1309,193,1927]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga hyaloptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; D, E, F. L. oxyptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. serrateiceps Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. valvata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov; P, Q, R. L. zebrina Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297910/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 8H</figureCitation>
). Scutellum mostly brownish yellow (
<figureCitation box="[989,1089,1690,1715]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[287,1308,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-106@21.[284,1309,193,1927]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga hyaloptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; D, E, F. L. oxyptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. serrateiceps Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. valvata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov; P, Q, R. L. zebrina Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297910/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 8H</figureCitation>
). Pleura, katepisternum, and mesopleuron mostly dark yellow (
<figureCitation box="[544,625,1726,1751]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[287,1308,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-106@21.[284,1309,193,1927]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga hyaloptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; D, E, F. L. oxyptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. serrateiceps Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. valvata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov; P, Q, R. L. zebrina Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297910/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 8I</figureCitation>
). Wing (
<figureCitation box="[727,819,1726,1751]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,918,1902]" captionTargetId="figure-448@17.[151,1436,918,1902]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 4. Wing of male: A. Leucophenga hyaloptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; B. L. oxyptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; C. L. platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; D. L. serrateiceps Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; E. L. valvata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; F. L. zebrina Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297902" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297902/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
): brownish distally; costal vein between R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1309,1333,1741,1755]" fontSize="6" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">2+3</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1412,1436,1741,1755]" fontSize="6" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">4+5</subScript>
distally with ca. 4–6 peg-like spinules on ventral surface; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[836,860,1780,1794]" fontSize="6" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">4+5</subScript>
and M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[944,952,1780,1794]" fontSize="6" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">1</subScript>
slightly convergent distally; halter mostly yellow (
<figureCitation box="[245,338,1803,1828]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1941,1963]" captionTargetBox="[287,1308,193,1927]" captionTargetId="figure-106@21.[284,1309,193,1927]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 8. Lateral view of head, dorsal and lateral views of thorax in males: A, B, C. Leucophenga hyaloptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; D, E, F. L. oxyptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G, H, I. L. platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. serrateiceps Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; M, N, O. L. valvata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov; P, Q, R. L. zebrina Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5297910" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5297910/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 8H</figureCitation>
). Abdominal tergites brown, 2nd tergite yellow anteriorly and laterally, 3rd to 5th tergites with yellow patches submedially and sublaterally (
<figureCitation box="[672,778,1839,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[309,1277,213,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-93@24.[291,1296,193,1910]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 11. Colour patterns of abdominal tergites: A, B, C. Leucophenga helvipecta Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; D, E. L. hyaloptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; F. L. oxyptera Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; G. L. platypyga Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; H, I. L. serrateiceps Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov.; J, K, L. L. valvata Huang &amp; Chen, sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5308389" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5308389/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Fig. 11G</figureCitation>
). Male terminalia: Epandrium pubescent, with ca. 9 setae near posterior and ventral margins per side (
