<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="56" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="55.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,332,357]" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">Etymology.</emphasis>
A combination of the Greek words: “ 
<emphasis box="[811,867,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">platy</emphasis>
” (= broad) and “ 
<emphasis box="[1089,1142,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="56">pyge</emphasis>
” (= pygal), referring to epandrium dorsally strongly expanded.
</paragraph>
